01:08.936 --> 01:12.712
- And over again, screaming
the F word in my face.

01:12.712 --> 01:13.545
Faggot,

01:14.648 --> 01:17.863
and it wasn't from the pain of the hitting

01:17.863 --> 01:21.497
or the word, god knows I've
heard that my whole life,

01:21.497 --> 01:23.975
but it was the fact that it was him,

01:23.975 --> 01:27.642
someone that I loved,
instead of a stranger.

01:33.813 --> 01:34.813
- Hi, there.

01:36.437 --> 01:38.772
You coming to join us?

01:38.772 --> 01:39.605
- Sorry.

01:41.700 --> 01:44.783
- One second, hang on, you guys, hey.

01:47.957 --> 01:48.790
Hey, hey.

01:49.865 --> 01:51.109
I know you.

01:51.109 --> 01:54.037
- No, I'm looking for someone,

01:54.037 --> 01:56.149
a girl, dark hair, kind of stand offish.

01:56.149 --> 01:58.020
- That's most of us here.

01:58.020 --> 02:00.261
- Yeah, she's different.

02:00.261 --> 02:02.917
- Wait, wait, I know you, though.

02:02.917 --> 02:05.061
Right, I know your face or something.

02:05.061 --> 02:06.062
- Maybe.

02:06.062 --> 02:07.673
- How?

02:07.673 --> 02:09.747
- Killed some people.

02:16.821 --> 02:19.525
- These are
gonna help you remember.

02:19.525 --> 02:23.275
Well, that is, whichever
one of you survives.

02:28.229 --> 02:30.396
Trust me, one of you will.

02:35.023 --> 02:37.919
See, the problem with memories,

02:37.919 --> 02:41.086
is the further you get away from them,

02:42.643 --> 02:45.107
the more they change,

02:45.107 --> 02:46.940
so you need reminders,

02:48.211 --> 02:50.960
something tangible, something that helps

02:50.960 --> 02:53.877
you keep the memory alive and well.

02:55.344 --> 02:57.177
Pictures, so tangible.

03:07.572 --> 03:08.655
Look at this.

03:10.901 --> 03:11.984
Look at that.

03:15.333 --> 03:17.555
Don't be so angry.

03:17.555 --> 03:19.909
I'm doing this for you.

03:19.909 --> 03:22.355
So you can remember.

03:22.355 --> 03:25.438
So you can remember and never forget.

03:31.286 --> 03:32.119
So pretty.

03:37.492 --> 03:39.575
So good at what she does.

03:45.895 --> 03:47.978
Let me ask you something.

03:50.327 --> 03:51.910
Do you feel heroic?

03:53.624 --> 03:55.957
Could you be a hero for her?

03:59.225 --> 04:01.475
Would you die for her, huh?

04:28.971 --> 04:30.183
- Boo.

04:30.183 --> 04:31.016
- Tim.

04:33.015 --> 04:35.862
- Hey, I mean, who else, right?

04:35.862 --> 04:39.695
Wow, man, smells of BO
and depression in here.

04:41.943 --> 04:45.026
Well, Nosferatu, you gonna let me in?

04:47.623 --> 04:51.373
All right, well how
about coming on out then?

04:53.863 --> 04:54.696
Scott?

04:55.814 --> 04:59.718
Seriously, come on, I'll buy you coffee.

04:59.718 --> 05:01.718
Whoa, whoa, pants first.

05:05.768 --> 05:06.889
Yeah.

05:06.889 --> 05:09.095
- Hey, Tim, wait here, please.

05:09.095 --> 05:11.262
- Yeah, okay, sure.
- Okay.

05:26.275 --> 05:27.971
- You look like shit.

05:27.971 --> 05:28.804
- Thanks.

05:30.434 --> 05:31.435
- Too blunt?

05:31.435 --> 05:33.268
- Yeah, just a little.

05:34.450 --> 05:36.450
- You getting any sleep?

05:38.515 --> 05:42.682
Is that an "I don't know"
or "I don't really care"?

05:43.731 --> 05:44.564
Oh, cool.

05:45.491 --> 05:48.115
Thanks for clearing that up.

05:48.115 --> 05:50.610
What about her parents?

05:50.610 --> 05:52.899
- They don't really want
anything to do with me.

05:52.899 --> 05:55.747
They just keep to themselves.

05:55.747 --> 05:57.830
I don't blame 'em really.

05:59.347 --> 06:01.443
- Well, they got each other.

06:01.443 --> 06:02.776
What do you got?

06:13.237 --> 06:16.320
What about one of those group things?

06:18.881 --> 06:21.714
What you call it, a support thing?

06:22.706 --> 06:26.039
- I don't really need anybody else, Tim.

06:27.608 --> 06:28.608
- Bull shit.

06:29.907 --> 06:33.251
Okay, you've got a guilty
conscience or nightmares

06:33.251 --> 06:36.754
or whatever, fine, that's your deal,

06:36.754 --> 06:38.291
but don't you for one fucking second

06:38.291 --> 06:41.347
try to tell me that
you don't need anybody,

06:41.347 --> 06:43.027
because sure as shit a month from now,

06:43.027 --> 06:44.291
when I haven't heard from you

06:44.291 --> 06:46.019
and I gotta get the cops
to open up your door,

06:46.019 --> 06:48.579
only to find your brains
painting the walls,

06:48.579 --> 06:52.995
it's gonna be too goddamn
late to say I told you so.

06:52.995 --> 06:56.354
So please, for the sake of my virgin soul,

06:56.354 --> 06:59.954
don't put me through that shit, man.

06:59.954 --> 07:01.912
Let me be the same asshole friend

07:01.912 --> 07:05.186
I've always been and let
me feel good about myself

07:05.186 --> 07:09.764
because I got you off your
ass and into recovery, huh?

07:17.736 --> 07:20.549
Yeah, this coffee tastes like shit.

07:41.907 --> 07:43.491
- I'm sorry.

07:43.491 --> 07:44.324
- Why?

07:53.333 --> 07:55.250
- It's okay, it's okay.

07:58.474 --> 07:59.641
It's not okay.

08:00.677 --> 08:01.894
It's not okay.

08:04.047 --> 08:04.880
It's not.

08:23.250 --> 08:24.417
- Not for you?

08:25.566 --> 08:26.567
- Excuse me?

08:26.567 --> 08:27.808
- You're not going in.

08:27.808 --> 08:29.744
- It's the wrong place.

08:29.744 --> 08:32.336
- Uh huh, good luck with that.

08:38.679 --> 08:42.006
Sitting off from the group now.

08:42.006 --> 08:45.921
Got any other bad trips you're going for?

08:45.921 --> 08:47.375
- Real supportive.

08:47.375 --> 08:48.530
- What?

08:48.530 --> 08:50.030
- Real supportive.

08:50.964 --> 08:52.596
- And?

08:52.596 --> 08:54.817
- For a support group.

08:54.817 --> 08:57.039
- Oh, these thing are total garbage.

08:57.039 --> 09:00.193
I just like calling
outsiders on their shit.

09:00.193 --> 09:01.634
- Then what are you doing here?

09:01.634 --> 09:03.216
- Good, good, good.
- Yeah.

09:03.216 --> 09:04.501
- Would you mind getting the door please?

09:04.501 --> 09:05.501
- Oh, sure.

09:05.501 --> 09:06.501
- Thank you.

09:10.738 --> 09:12.571
We're in a safe space.

09:13.521 --> 09:15.700
Whatever exists in the outside world

09:15.700 --> 09:19.533
and wants to cause you
harm stops at the door.

09:20.837 --> 09:25.138
This is an environment
free of judgment and fear,

09:25.138 --> 09:28.319
where we're all welcome
to share or just listen,

09:28.319 --> 09:30.097
whatever you're comfortable with.

09:30.097 --> 09:34.772
My name is Paul and I welcome
you all to our sanctuary.

09:34.772 --> 09:36.913
- Hi, Paul.
- Thank you, Paul.

09:36.913 --> 09:38.784
- Thank you, Paul.

09:38.784 --> 09:39.617
- Hello.

09:41.712 --> 09:42.785
- Hi.

09:42.785 --> 09:43.618
- Welcome.

09:44.740 --> 09:45.573
- Thanks.

09:46.642 --> 09:47.475
- And you?

09:48.880 --> 09:50.577
Glad you've returned.

09:50.577 --> 09:51.410
- Uh uh.

09:53.585 --> 09:54.418
- Well.

09:55.889 --> 09:59.032
Would anyone like to
share any recent struggles

09:59.032 --> 10:02.365
or successes you've had in recent weeks?

10:05.811 --> 10:07.169
You don't need to raise your hand.

10:07.169 --> 10:08.833
- Yeah, I'm curious.

10:08.833 --> 10:10.449
- Your name?

10:10.449 --> 10:12.032
- What, no I'm not.

10:14.179 --> 10:15.012
I'm Scott.

10:16.546 --> 10:17.713
- Welcome, Scott.

10:17.713 --> 10:20.385
- Welcome, Scott.

10:20.385 --> 10:21.218
- Thanks.

10:23.455 --> 10:26.321
So I'm curious how long
you have people been coming

10:26.321 --> 10:27.889
here for.

10:27.889 --> 10:30.641
- It ranges anywhere from a few months

10:30.641 --> 10:33.391
to going on two years for myself.

10:34.257 --> 10:35.090
- Years?

10:36.305 --> 10:37.839
- Some people find themselves dropping in

10:37.839 --> 10:41.921
from time to time as a way
to recharge your batteries,

10:41.921 --> 10:43.793
or even measure your growth.

10:43.793 --> 10:46.528
- Does anyone ever stop?

10:46.528 --> 10:47.529
- Stop?

10:47.529 --> 10:48.753
- Stop coming.

10:48.753 --> 10:51.086
Does anyone ever get better?

10:53.489 --> 10:57.605
- It's not really a one and done solution.

10:57.605 --> 10:59.407
This is support.

10:59.407 --> 11:01.183
We help each other.

11:01.183 --> 11:04.404
Through our common bonds,
the things that unite us.

11:04.404 --> 11:05.237
- Tragedy.

11:06.548 --> 11:07.761
- Birds of a feather.

11:07.761 --> 11:09.678
- Misery loves company.

11:10.608 --> 11:14.775
- I notice some trepidation
coming from you, doubt.

11:16.832 --> 11:19.539
Your trauma was recent.

11:19.539 --> 11:21.633
- Are you asking?

11:21.633 --> 11:23.550
- Don't really have to.

11:26.479 --> 11:28.497
Please, if you would share with the group

11:28.497 --> 11:30.830
what brought you here today.

11:33.778 --> 11:35.528
Someone close to you.

11:36.881 --> 11:37.964
- My husband.

11:39.280 --> 11:40.363
Car accident.

11:42.979 --> 11:47.146
- I'm Joe, my brother died
from a heroin overdose.

11:48.785 --> 11:51.780
- I'm Sherri, I lost my
sister six months ago

11:51.780 --> 11:53.280
to a drunk driver.

11:55.553 --> 11:58.053
- Tragedy can shape our lives,

11:59.423 --> 12:04.084
but so to happiness can shape
our experience of death.

12:04.084 --> 12:06.084
- Tell that to the dead.

12:08.516 --> 12:10.117
- You blame yourself.

12:10.117 --> 12:10.950
- What?

12:12.193 --> 12:16.418
- I sense that you carry
a lot of blame with you.

12:16.418 --> 12:18.835
Do you feel a responsibility?

12:20.084 --> 12:20.917
- No.

12:22.735 --> 12:25.156
- Please, don't close up.

12:25.156 --> 12:28.768
It's important that you
remain open and honest,

12:28.768 --> 12:29.777
even if you're scared.

12:29.777 --> 12:31.194
- I'm not scared.

12:32.928 --> 12:34.368
I'm not.

12:35.745 --> 12:36.578
I'm done.

12:49.364 --> 12:50.819
What?

12:52.531 --> 12:53.667
What?

12:58.115 --> 12:58.948
Stupid.

13:08.578 --> 13:09.411
What?

13:11.347 --> 13:12.659
- Why?

13:14.883 --> 13:17.411
- Hey, thank you for returning.

13:17.411 --> 13:18.244
- Sure.

13:19.554 --> 13:21.763
- I know it might not seem like much

13:21.763 --> 13:25.508
but it really is big accomplishment.

13:25.508 --> 13:26.425
Sorry, I...

13:28.615 --> 13:30.532
Door please, thank you.

13:33.043 --> 13:35.667
Now, we're all in a safe place.

13:35.667 --> 13:37.026
Whatever exists in the outside world

13:37.026 --> 13:40.435
that wants to bring you
harm stops at the door.

13:40.435 --> 13:44.003
This is an environment free of judgment.

13:44.003 --> 13:46.499
- It's like everybody else knows now,

13:46.499 --> 13:48.999
and the blood is in the water,

13:49.843 --> 13:52.420
and the sharks are coming out to feed

13:52.420 --> 13:54.804
and they just keep picking at me,

13:54.804 --> 13:57.221
like piece by piece by piece.

13:58.163 --> 14:01.026
- A predatory response is not uncommon

14:01.026 --> 14:04.053
for survivors, sort of a resentment

14:04.053 --> 14:05.429
from the rest of the world.

14:05.429 --> 14:07.179
- But I'm the victim.

14:10.098 --> 14:11.848
- Something to share?

14:15.860 --> 14:17.557
Do you feel like a victim?

14:17.557 --> 14:18.474
- Fuck off.

14:19.843 --> 14:21.461
Sorry, didn't mean to make it--

14:21.461 --> 14:22.706
- No, no, it's all right.

14:22.706 --> 14:24.179
It's a knee jerk reaction, I'm sure,

14:24.179 --> 14:27.075
but it's part of a
guard you're putting up.

14:27.075 --> 14:28.675
- Well, yeah, you have to keep up a guard

14:28.675 --> 14:30.008
otherwise you...

14:33.426 --> 14:34.843
- Otherwise what?

14:36.099 --> 14:39.315
- Otherwise you become a victim forever,

14:39.315 --> 14:41.763
and I don't want that.

14:41.763 --> 14:43.698
- Well then what do you want?

14:43.698 --> 14:45.115
Put a name to it.

14:48.295 --> 14:49.128
- Justice.

14:50.806 --> 14:52.819
But there's no such thing.

14:52.819 --> 14:54.275
- What makes you say that?

14:54.275 --> 14:55.797
- Because does anybody ever get it?

14:55.797 --> 14:57.214
I don't get mine.

14:59.330 --> 15:03.970
I wake up every single
morning in a cold sweat.

15:03.970 --> 15:06.403
I see things that aren't there.

15:06.403 --> 15:09.035
I live in constant fear
that he is at my door

15:09.035 --> 15:10.419
and that he's coming back.

15:10.419 --> 15:12.919
- They do come back, the dead.

15:14.691 --> 15:17.858
To remind us what they gave up for us,

15:18.914 --> 15:21.507
or what we gave them up for.

15:21.507 --> 15:23.250
- What?

15:23.250 --> 15:26.836
- I was saying that justice
can come in many forms.

15:26.836 --> 15:28.610
Are you familiar with the philosophy

15:28.610 --> 15:32.738
that the best revenge
is to lead a good life?

15:32.738 --> 15:34.291
- Night.

15:34.291 --> 15:36.067
- If you were given the chance

15:36.067 --> 15:38.650
to get your justice, would you?

15:40.818 --> 15:42.235
- Hypothetically?

15:46.563 --> 15:47.480
Yeah, sure.

15:48.450 --> 15:50.644
- He gave you a choice.

15:50.644 --> 15:52.098
I know what happened to you.

15:52.098 --> 15:53.490
- No, you don't.

15:53.490 --> 15:54.883
You didn't have a psycho in your house,

15:54.883 --> 15:57.682
taking pictures, spouting philosophy.

15:57.682 --> 15:59.099
- How did it end?

16:04.482 --> 16:06.482
Come back inside.

16:06.482 --> 16:07.315
Share that

16:08.867 --> 16:12.117
and I'll let you in on a little secret.

16:15.490 --> 16:16.490
- All right.

16:17.911 --> 16:18.828
I'll do it.

16:21.203 --> 16:25.120
I was coming home and I
was excited to see her,

16:26.866 --> 16:30.699
my fiancee, and there
was a knock at the door.

16:36.503 --> 16:37.836
She answered it,

16:40.135 --> 16:41.385
and he hit her,

16:42.504 --> 16:45.337
and I tried to fight back but I...

16:51.230 --> 16:53.147
He caught me off guard,

16:54.653 --> 16:56.403
and then he bound us,

16:59.375 --> 17:00.875
and threatened us.

17:05.184 --> 17:06.351
Took pictures.

17:08.270 --> 17:10.936
He asked me would I die for her.

17:16.996 --> 17:18.246
And I said yes.

17:23.142 --> 17:24.892
And it didn't matter.

17:25.789 --> 17:27.289
I watched her die,

17:28.932 --> 17:32.849
and there was nothing
that I could do about it.

17:36.423 --> 17:38.340
And then, he just left.

17:44.488 --> 17:48.199
And I was alone with her body for so long.

17:53.639 --> 17:56.222
And I just stared right at her,

17:59.786 --> 18:01.953
and she stared back at me.

18:05.556 --> 18:06.806
She still does.

18:10.467 --> 18:12.467
- Thank you for sharing.

18:13.778 --> 18:15.945
- I don't feel any better.

18:17.331 --> 18:18.531
- It takes time.

18:18.531 --> 18:20.691
- I'm running out.

18:20.691 --> 18:24.353
- Don't let the
darkness overtake you.

18:24.353 --> 18:26.270
- What if I want it to?

18:30.099 --> 18:32.766
- So here's the damnedest thing.

18:33.908 --> 18:36.882
You and I share the same monster.

18:41.109 --> 18:44.835
Physical traits, any
details you can remember.

18:44.835 --> 18:45.837
- No, I can't.

18:45.837 --> 18:46.837
It's a blur.

18:46.837 --> 18:48.403
One minute he's six feet tall in my mind,

18:48.403 --> 18:50.883
and the next, he's barely six inches.

18:50.883 --> 18:52.882
It shifts, nothing's concrete.

18:52.882 --> 18:53.799
- Hispanic?

18:54.833 --> 18:55.835
- I don't know.

18:55.835 --> 18:56.914
- Mark on his wrist?

18:56.914 --> 18:57.916
- Yeah, maybe.

18:57.916 --> 19:00.371
- Takes Polaroids while
spouting philosophy.

19:00.371 --> 19:01.373
- Yes, but it--

19:01.373 --> 19:02.290
- It's him.

19:04.579 --> 19:06.412
- What'd he do to you?

19:07.620 --> 19:09.787
- Take a 16 year old girl,

19:10.818 --> 19:13.603
screwed in the head, runs away from home,

19:13.603 --> 19:16.686
heads west until the ocean stops her.

19:17.750 --> 19:20.167
There on the beach she meets,

19:21.416 --> 19:24.833
can't say handsome but engaging stranger.

19:26.897 --> 19:29.316
He fills her ear with beautiful thoughts

19:29.316 --> 19:33.107
and promises she never thought possible,

19:33.107 --> 19:36.866
gets her to follow him
back to his compound,

19:36.866 --> 19:39.033
for lack of a better word,

19:40.085 --> 19:43.585
and there, she finds plenty of other naive

19:45.922 --> 19:47.422
like minded girls.

19:49.539 --> 19:52.706
It's basically his own personal harem.

19:53.667 --> 19:58.003
He spouts philosophical nonsense
and they can't get enough.

19:58.003 --> 19:59.411
- You good?

19:59.411 --> 20:00.661
- Borrow a pen.

20:06.960 --> 20:07.793
Go away.

20:10.560 --> 20:12.310
So our little runaway

20:15.891 --> 20:19.966
starts to see tears in
the fabric of his lies,

20:19.966 --> 20:23.084
and pushes, but he's got the others

20:23.084 --> 20:26.667
so wrapped up tight
that they keep her down

20:28.465 --> 20:30.109
and she realizes she can't get out

20:30.109 --> 20:31.776
not without trouble.

20:34.001 --> 20:37.418
So one night, when the others are asleep,

20:39.245 --> 20:40.995
she creeps downstairs

20:42.369 --> 20:45.702
and pulls the gas main out of the stove.

20:48.157 --> 20:49.574
It leaks a while,

20:50.734 --> 20:54.067
and then she lights a fire and it works.

20:55.964 --> 20:57.464
There are screams.

21:01.137 --> 21:02.594
Flames.

21:02.594 --> 21:03.511
People die.

21:05.040 --> 21:07.424
Some get away, maybe even him.

21:07.424 --> 21:10.788
She doesn't know, not for a long time,

21:10.788 --> 21:14.227
not until she finds
herself at a group meeting

21:14.227 --> 21:17.191
and hears the boy in front tell a story

21:17.191 --> 21:20.882
about her monster and then she knows,

21:20.882 --> 21:23.715
he got out and he's hurting again.

21:26.609 --> 21:30.418
And maybe, just maybe, she's met the one

21:30.418 --> 21:31.957
other person in the whole world who'd do

21:31.957 --> 21:35.074
anything to help her stop him.

21:35.074 --> 21:36.729
- It's a good story.

21:36.729 --> 21:38.725
Yeah, is it true?

21:38.725 --> 21:40.694
- That's on his wrist.

21:48.363 --> 21:50.270
- Who are you?

21:50.270 --> 21:51.738
- O.

21:51.738 --> 21:53.905
- Oh, like the expression?

21:54.778 --> 21:56.278
- Like the letter.

21:57.323 --> 21:59.005
Or the story.

21:59.005 --> 22:00.755
- What story?
- Of O.

22:01.961 --> 22:04.621
- Get out of here, it's...

22:04.621 --> 22:05.788
- You with me?

22:08.651 --> 22:10.401
- You know who he is?

22:11.546 --> 22:13.515
You know where to find him.

22:23.392 --> 22:24.225
- Maybe.

22:26.864 --> 22:28.049
- Why maybe?

22:28.049 --> 22:29.549
- Personal belief.

22:32.146 --> 22:34.396
Takes a killer to make one.

23:03.926 --> 23:06.342
You still live here, even after.

23:06.342 --> 23:08.757
- Yeah, I know, it's crazy, it's...

23:08.757 --> 23:11.783
- You don't have to explain yourself.

23:22.353 --> 23:25.091
You still keep all her things up, too.

23:28.353 --> 23:30.686
Just in case she comes back?

23:31.589 --> 23:32.422
- Yeah.

